sample_description: Collection site: Jaguaribe River Mangrove, Ceara state. City: Fortim. Estate: Ceara. Description of sampling site: Jaguaribe river mangrove is located in a estuary with an area of 1,735 km2. This ecosystem is impacted by the presence of shrimp farms, urban areas and runoff from agricultural areas. The soil was collected 3 km from the river mouth in a region with the presence of typical mangrove vegetation with the species Rhizophora mangle and Avicennia schaueriana.
study_title: Metagenomes isolated from NE Brazil

sample_description: Lutjanus argentimaculatus, commonly referred to as the mangrove jack or mangrove red snapper, is a type of marine ray-finned fish belonging to the Lutjanidae family. L. argentimaculatus, with its wide tropical and sub-tropical Indo-Pacific range, inhabits diverse and extensive geographical areas. The current resources for L. argentimaculatus lacks the whole genome sequence. This bioproject consists of the high-throughput sequence data, generated and used in the assembly and annotation of L. argentimaculatus
study_title: Lutjanus argentimaculatus Genome sequencing and assembly
